1.   Soiled or laundered clothes and linens; wash. 2.  a.   A commercial establishment for laundering clothes or linens. b.   A room or area, as in a house, for doing the wash. 1.  a place where clothes and linen are washed and ironed 2.  the clothes or linen washed and ironed 3.  the act of laundering    1.   articles of clothing, linens, etc., that have been or are to be washed.     2.   a business establishment where clothes, linens, etc., are laundered.     3.   a room or area, as in a home or apartment building, reserved for doing the family wash. 